%md

### Turn CSV file into a SQLite database for fast query

msg.data: Turn CSV file into a SQLite database for fast query

paragraphs.title: Parse CSV to SQLite DB
paragraphs.text:
%python

import sqlite3
import csv
import time

db = base_data_dir + "/data.db"
table_name = "data"
with sqlite3.connect(db) as conn:
    with open(csv_file, 'rb') as f:
        conn.execute("DROP TABLE IF EXISTS " + table_name)
        f.readline()
        conn.execute("CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS %s (" % table_name +
                "ID                      INTEGER," +
                "FIRST_NAME              TEXT," +
                "LAST_NAME               TEXT," +
                "EMAIL                   TEXT," +
                "GENDER                  TEXT," +
                "AGE                     INTEGER," +
                "SCHOOL                  TEXT," +
                "RELIGIOUS_BACKGROUND    TEXT," +
                "DENOMINATION            TEXT," +
                "CHURCH_NAME             TEXT," +
                "HOBBIES                 TEXT," +
                "CITY                    TEXT," +
                "COUNTRY                 TEXT," +
                "POSTAL_CODE             TEXT," +
                "CONVERSATION_START      INTEGER," +
                "CONVERSATION_END        INTEGER," +
                "CONVERSATION_TOPIC      TEXT," +
                "CONVERSATION_RATING     INTEGER," +
                "CONVERSATION_OUTCOME    TEXT," +
                "GRADE                   INTEGER" +
            ")")
        csv_reader = csv.reader(f, delimiter=",")
        for line in csv_reader:
            values = list()
            for i in range(len(line)):
                if "\"" in line[i]:
                    line[i] = line[i].replace("\"","'")
                if i in [0, 5, 18, 20]:
                    values.append(str(line[i]))
                elif i == 14:
                    continue
                elif i in [15, 16]:
                    values.append(str(time.mktime(time.strptime(line[14] + " " + line[i], "%m/%d/%Y %H:%M"))))
                else:
                    values.append("\"" + line[i] + "\"")
            try:
                conn.execute("INSERT INTO data VALUES (%s)" % ",".join(values))
            except:
                print "INSERT INTO data VALUES (%s)" % ",".join(values)
    conn.commit()
